  <archetypedescription>
    <p>
      <emph>
	Our enemies walk amongst us brothers, and we must root them out
	root and branch.  We must match our intellect against theirs
	in a battle as desperate as any between armies of serried ranks.
	The mighty fight with swords.  We fight in the shadows for the hearts,
	minds and souls of man.
      </emph>      
    </p>
    <p>
      <emph>
	The end of times is upon us brothers.   All we have left is
	to meet our makers on terms of our own choosing; fighting
	against the darkness or cowering in our beds.  May
	Mithras grant us the strength to hold our course.
      </emph>      
    </p>

    <p>
      The Black Coats have cultivated a reputation for being itinerant preachers, turning their
      backs on the greater Mithratic Church organization with its corruption and bureaucracy, in order
      to take the word of Mithras directly to the people.  However, this reputation is a carefully crafted
      façade designed to shield the Black Cloaks from closer scrutiny as they implement their
      machiavellian designs, playing politics like princes play at a Tamerlane board.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      More formally known as the The Lesser Brothers of Saint Ansgar, the Black Coats are one of a
      group of orders known collectively as Ansgarians.  The Lesser Brothers are a well educated,
      well organized, though comparatively poor offshoot of the Church of Mithras.  They are a non-monastic
      order, working among the common people, and are supported by donations, charities and managed funds.
      Their current leader is the Minister General, Theophilus Reisinger, who resides in the fortress like
      Loc-Mitras Abbey in Laibstadt.      
    </p>
    
    <p>
      The founder of the Black Cloaks, Joachim Ansgar had a successul military career in the Westreich Guard.
      Ansgar had an epiphany, during a white plague fever dream.   In his fifties, he sold his commission
      in the military, donated his army pension to the local temple of Mithras and founded the Black Cloaks.
      His teachings primarily concern the need to be watchful for the enemies of the church and to protect
      mankind.  There words aare Vigilate et Custodiat and the mark of the order is a Sword and Lantern.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      Black Coats are bound by the Asanguinous Dictat, though Ansgar raves against it at length in his
      writings.  Black Coats are allowed to wear armour.  Though being a mendicant order, whose members hold
      vowsof asceticism, the use of expensive armour is frowned upon.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      The Lesser Brothers of Saint Ansgar often work closely with the broader church of Mithras.  The organization
      seeks to place its members in positions of power to enable it to more effectively defend the people.  Additionally,
      it is rumoured to have an extensive intelligence network.  It has been accussed on a number of occassions
      of involving itself in political intrigue though the majority of the populace see its motivations as benign.
    </p>

